This article summarizes the remarks made by President Ram Nath Kovind of India and President Donald Trump of the United States during President Trump's state visit to India. President Kovind warmly welcomes President Trump and expresses gratitude for his visit. He mentions the significant attention and interest generated by President Trump's visit and highlights the positive impact of events like the "Howdy Modi" and "Namaste Trump" gatherings on strengthening the relationship between India and the United States. President Trump acknowledges the warm reception and expresses his gratitude for the productive work done during his visit. He praises India as a great country and emphasizes the strong bilateral relationship between the two nations, particularly in terms of trade and military cooperation. Both presidents express their appreciation for each other and the special bond between India and the United States.